e of 500 (Internal Server Error). This is not overly informative."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"HTTPError","anchor":"HTTPError"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hummingbird uses the Error object "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/documentation\/Hummingbird\/HTTPError","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" throughout its codebase. The server recognises this and can generate a more informative response for the client from it. The error includes the status code that should be returned and a response message if needed. For example"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["router.get(\"user\") { request, context -> User in","    guard let userId = request.uri.queryParameters.get(\"id\", as: Int.self) else {","        throw HTTPError(.badRequest, message: \"Invalid user id\")","    }","    ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HTTPError"},{"text":" generated here will be recognised by the server and it will generate a status code 400 (Bad Request) with the body “Invalid user id”.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"HTTPResponseError","anchor":"HTTPResponseError"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The server knows how to respond to a ","type":"text"},{"code":"HTTPError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" because it conforms to protocol ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/documentation\/Hummingbird\/HTTPResponseError","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". You can create your own ","type":"text"},{"code":"Error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" object and conform it to ","type":"text"},{"code":"HTTPResponseError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and the server will know how to generate a sensible error from it. The example below is a error class that outputs an error code in the response headers.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sw